    "id": "2076598139801190514",
    "text": "GLOBAL REFINING margins are nearing record highs following the breakdown of the ceasefire between the United States and Iran, and Ukraine’s attacks on Russia’s oil refineries. In the United States, the crack spread for turning three barrels of WTI crude into two barrels of gasoline and one barrel of diesel has averaged $61 per barrel so far in July. After adjusting for inflation, the benchmark 3-2-1 crack is the second-highest on record after $64 in June 2022, shortly after Russia’s full-scale invasion of Ukraine and the imposition of sanctions by the United States and Europe in response:",
